# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

## [0.5.0] 2020-10-08
### Added
- btrfs support (this file system is not recommended for not experienced users!)
### Changed
- wget to curl for download this script in README.md file
### Fixed
- Time zone menu list (more Cities visible per line)
- Kernel menu does not exit to previous section after choosing Kernel
### Removed
- n/a

## [0.4.0] 2020-10-06
### Added
- CHANGELOG file
- Separators
- different Kernel support! (Stable, Zen, Longterm, Hardened)
### Changed
- PyArchLinux ASCII logo
- rebuild connection checker
### Fixed
- setup file visibility after installation
### Removed
- temporary removed some Desktop Environments

## [0.3.0] 2020-05-12
### Added
- color support for installer
- setup variables
- connection checker
- locale support
- keymap support
- network support
- multilib support
- dhcp support
- wifi support
- PPPoE support
- mobile broadbands support
- all added things from 0.2.0 [testing branch]
### Changed
- rebuild user management menu
- rebuild Desktop Environments menu
- rebuild Video drivers menu
- rebuild Display Manager menu
- rebuild main menu
### Fixed
- visual fixes
### Removed
- temporary removed some Desktop Environments

## [0.2.0] [testing branch - unreleased] - 2020-05-12
### Added
- Disk management - list of disks
- Disk mounting - list of disks
- NVidia - nvidia-settings package
- xorg - xorg-xrandr, arandr packages
- lightdm - lightdm-gtk-greeter-settings package
- Audio - PulseAudio support with ALSA
- Audacious - added plugins
### Changed
- PyArchLinux ASCII logo
- rebuild main menu
### Fixed
- visual fixes
### Removed
- locale variables

## [0.1.0] - 2020-04-22
### Added
- Initial release
- PyArchLinux ASCII logo
- Disk managment
- Disk mounting
- Video drivers support (NVidia, AMD, Intel, VirtualBox)
- Desktop Environments
- Initial configuration
- Bootloader (grub)
- User management
### Changed
- n/a
### Fixed
- n/a
### Removed
- n/a